The paper presents a reinforcement learning approach to solve the unit commitment problem, which involves optimizing the scheduling of power generation units. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (specifically reinforcement learning), artificial intelligence, control systems, distributed computing, and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
